data.chText: （演员、运动员）首次亮相；初次登台（或上场）
data.enText: the first public appearance of a performer or sports player

data.chText: 本周他将在第一支出场的队伍中首次亮相。
data.enText: He will make his debut for the first team this week.

data.chText: 这个乐队首次推出的专辑

tr: the act of beginning something new
example: they looked forward to the debut of their new product line

tr: the presentation of a debutante in society
appear for the first time in public
example: The new ballet that debuts next months at Covent Garden, is already sold out
This young soprano debuts next month at the Metropolitan Opera

tr: present for the first time to the public
example: The band debuts a new song or two each month

value.def: The debut of a performer or sports player is their first public performance, appearance, or recording.

example.ex: Dundee United's Dave Bowman makes his international debut.
example.tran: 邓迪联队的戴夫·鲍曼首次亮相国际比赛。
她的首张专辑《甜蜜时光》

value.tran: (表演者或运动员的）首次登台，初次露面；（歌手的）首次录音

trans: 首张专辑；专辑；处女专辑；第一张个人专辑
